<F P=100> ITALY &amp; VATICAN CITY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Offers Troops To UN Standing Army </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Offers Troops To UN Standing Army </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1304221494 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 2135 GMT 
13 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1304221494 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Televideo Teletext </F>
<F P=105>  Italian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Italy has offered to supply troops to a UN standing 
army. More than 15 countries have already placed troops at the 
UN's disposal, and 54,000 soldiers could be rapidly deployed in 
peacekeeping operations. 
  The UN plans to have 100,000 blue helmets by the end of the 
year. They will be used where both sides in a conflict ask for 
their intervention. The contingent being offered by Italy would 
largely be made up of medical personnel. Seventy thousand 
troops are currently deployed by the United Nations. 

</TEXT>

