<H3> <TI>   Tirana Demands Embassy Reductions </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Tirana Demands Embassy Reductions </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1304164094 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in 
Greek 1500 GMT 13 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1304164094 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Tirana regime is escalating tension in 
Greek-Albanian relations despite Greece's intentions to foster 
good relations. In a provocative diplomatic note to the Greek 
Embassy in Tirana, the Albanian Government asked the Greek 
ambassador to reduce the embassy's diplomatic staff from 10 to 
six people. 
  According to a REUTER dispatch from Tirana, the diplomatic 
note says that, because there has been no agreement on the 
question of the diplomatic staff, the Albanian side believes 
that there should be a reciprocal reduction in the staff of the 
Greek and Albanian diplomatic missions from 10 to six people. 
The Albanian note also gives Athens a 10-day time limit to 
carry out the reduction. REUTER also notes that Albania has a 
four-member diplomatic mission in Athens. 

</TEXT>

