<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Spokesman Says NATO Intervention `Appropriate' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Spokesman Says NATO Intervention `Appropriate' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1304112894 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1000 
GMT 13 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1304112894 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Text] Turkey has declared that the NATO intervention 
against Serbian positions is an appropriate and welcome 
development, even though it is a belated move. It was stated 
that Turkey's insistent attitude played a significant role in 
the realization of this intervention. 
  In his weekly news conference, Foreign Ministry Spokesman 
Ferhat Ataman said that Gorazde is one of the Serbs' main 
targets in their policy to gain territory and carry out ethnic 
cleansing. This is why Gorazde was included among the six safe 
areas declared by the UN Security Council and was placed under 
international protection, Ataman recalled. 
  Although it was a belated move, Ataman declared, the NATO 
intervention against Serbian positions was an appropriate and 
welcome development. He added that Turkey's insistent attitude 
constituted one of the significant factors in the realization of 
this intervention. 
  Ataman stated: It is important to closely observe the Serbs' 
every move and behavior and to give the necessary response to 
every attack. The international community should have realized 
by now that the Serbs understand only determined stands. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

