<F P=100> Germany </F>
<H3> <TI>   Butrus-Ghali Backs German Position </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Butrus-Ghali Backs German Position </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1304150394 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1206 GMT 13 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1304150394 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DDP/ADN) -- UN Secretary General Butrus 
Butrus-Ghali has spoken in support of Germany becoming a 
permanent member of the UN Security Council [UNSC]. This was, 
however, a purely personal view, Butrus-Ghali said after a talk 
with German Foreign Minister Klaus Kinkel in Bonn today. The 
decision on this issue lay with the UN General Assembly, he said. 
  Butrus-Ghali underlined the United Nations' desire that 
Germany should play a greater role in international UN missions. 
He hoped that the constitutional clarification needed for this 
is achieved soon and that Germany will then also be able to 
participate fully in UN missions. 

</TEXT>

