<H3> <TI>   Claes, 'Arafat Discuss Mideast Peace Process </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Claes, 'Arafat Discuss Mideast Peace Process </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BR1404131194 Brussels BELGA Database in French 1719 GMT 13 
Apr 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR1404131194 </F>
<F P=104>  Brussels BELGA Database </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Article signed MPK/RHR: "Claes and 'Arafat Discuss </F>
Difficulties Encountered by Middle East Peace Process"] 
  [Text] Brussels, 13 Apr (BELGA) -- Belgian Foreign Minister 
Willy Claes spoke with PLO Chairman Yasir 'Arafat in Strasbourg 
on Wednesday, 13 April, of the difficulties encountered in the 
Middle East peace process, according to a communique from the 
Belgian Foreign Ministry. 
  Mr. Claes stressed "the need to convince all parties to 
achieve rapid progress in this process," the communique stressed. 
  The Belgian minister also reminded 'Arafat that he fully 
supports the idea of European Union (EU) funding for the 
Palestinian police force, a matter on which the EU ministers 
must soon decide. He also stressed the importance of a prompt 
and concrete implementation of projects benefitting the 
Palestinian population in the occupied territories which the EU 
has already agreed to finance, the communique added. 

</TEXT>

