<H3> <TI>   Kohl Receives Polish Prime Minister for Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kohl Receives Polish Prime Minister for Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1404110694 Hamburg DPA in German 0921 GMT 14 Apr 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1404110694 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DPA) -- At the beginning of his two-day visit 
to Germany, Polish Prime Minister Waldemar Pawlak met Helmut 
Kohl on Thursday [14 April]. In their talks, Kohl and his guest 
will mainly discuss the extension of economic relations and 
Poland's desire for early European Union membership. Poland's 
wish to get closer to NATO will also be discussed. 
  During his first official visit to Germany, Pawlak will also 
meet representatives of the Federation of German Chambers of 
Industry and Commerce, Bundestag President Rita Suessmuth, and 
Hans-Ulrich Klose, chairman of the Social Democratic Party of 
Germany Bundestag group. Pawlak will hold more economic talks 
in Stuttgart, where he is scheduled to arrive tomorrow. 

</TEXT>

