<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Germany </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bundesbank Cuts Discount, Lombard Rates </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Bundesbank Cuts Discount, Lombard Rates </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1404145494 Hamburg DPA in German 1246 GMT 14 Apr 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1404145494 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Frankfurt/Main (DPA) -- At its session in Frankfurt 
on Thursday [14 April], the Central Bank Council of the German 
Bundesbank cut the prime rate by 0.25 percentage points. As of 
Friday, the discount rate will be reduced from 5.25 percent to 
5.0 percent, and the Lombard rate from 6.75 to 6.5 percent. 
  With its decision, the Central Bank Councils has "responded 
to the fact that the prospects for another decrease in the rate 
of price increases have improved." In addition, the Bundesbank 
assumes that the growth in the money supply will continue to 
slow down following the distortions at the turn of the year that 
were the result of special factors. 
  On Thursday, the Bundesbank also announced that in the 1993 
fiscal year, the Bundesbank achieved 18.83 billion German marks 
[DM] in net earnings, of which DM18.6 billion were transferred 
to the accounts of the Federal Government. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

