<H3> <TI>   Government Welcomes Interest Rate Reduction </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Welcomes Interest Rate Reduction </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1404154694 Hamburg DPA in German 1318 GMT 14 Apr 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1404154694 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DPA) -- The Federal Government on Thursday 
[14 April] welcomed the reduction of the prime rate by the 
Bundesbank. The decision of the Central Bank Council to reduce 
the discount rate from 5.25 to 5 percent and the Lombard rate 
from 6.75 to 6.5 percent supports the Federal Government in its 
efforts for a further strengthening of the forces of growth, FRG 
Finance Minister Theo Waigel stated. 
  Economics Minister Guenter Rexrodt called on all people 
involved in economic circles to further orient their decisions 
toward the goal of stability. The inflation rate in both parts 
of Germany, which has been constantly declining since the 
beginning of 1993, as well as the Federal Government's 
consistent adherence to its policy of consolidation and the 
course of this years wage negotiations, so far have made the 
current reduction of interest rates easier. The interest rate 
reduction will support the forces of upswing in the economy. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

