BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Thaw in Trade With Iran"] </F>
  [Text] On Tuesday [12 April], during Iranian Foreign 
Minister 'Ali Akbar Velayati's visit to Austria, the interest of 
the media focused on human rights and the Rushdie case. 
However, during Velayati's talk with Economics Minister 
Schuessel, the focus was on the revival of Austrian-Iranian 
trade: In 1993 Austria's exports to Iran decreased by 20 
percent and imports even by 29 percent. The reason was Iranian 
payment difficulties and, as a result, nonliability by the 
Austrian Control Bank. In mid-March at least the obstacle of 
financing and liability was overcome: In bilateral negotiations 
in mid-March, Austria rescheduled Iranian debts amounting to 5 
million schillings. 

</TEXT>

