<H3> <TI>   Stinger Missiles for Turkey Confirmed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Stinger Missiles for Turkey Confirmed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1404194794 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1350 GMT 14 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1404194794 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Hamburg (DDP/ADN) -- The Hamburg customs authority 
has confirmed the planned shipment of 212 Stinger missiles to 
Turkey via Hamburg. All the necessary documents are on hand, 
thus there are no further obstacles to the shipment, a customs 
spokesman said this afternoon. The containers of missiles are 
due to arrive in Hamburg by rail on the morning of 16 April. 
  The Hamburg Green-Alternative List (GAL) were the first to 
become aware of the missile export, which involves missiles 
manufactured by the firm of Dornier in Friedrichshafen, the GAL 
said. They are to be shipped directly to Turkey on a Turkish 
ship. The GAL called upon the German Government and the Hamburg 
City Council to prevent the shipment. A council spokesman said 
that, as far as this issue is concerned, "They would not get 
involved in federal matters." 

</TEXT>

