<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   U.S. Envoy Lamb Continues Talks on CBM's </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    U.S. Envoy Lamb Continues Talks on CBM's </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Turkey's Ulucevik Comments </H4>

<F P=102> NC1404201194 Nicosia BRTK Television Network in Turkish 1630 
GMT 14 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1404201194 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia BRTK Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tugay Ulucevik, deputy under secretary of the 
Turkish Foreign Ministry, conferred with Robert Lamb, U.S. State 
Department special coordinator on Cyprus, this morning. The 
meeting, which continued for nearly two hours, was held in the 
Turkish Embassy in Nicosia. Ulucevik said after the meeting 
that he and Lamb were in Cyprus at the same time by coincidence. 
He also said that he exchanged views with Lamb, with whom he 
has been constantly in touch. Ulucevik stated the following: 
  [Begin Ulucevik recording] I have found an opportunity to 
bring to Ambassador Lamb's attention the significant changes 
that have been made between the original package of 
confidence-building measures and the package that is on the 
negotiating table at the present time. As far as I am 
concerned, our talks have been useful. Yes, that is how we have 
benefited from the courtesy meeting we had. [end recording] 
  A correspondent asked Ulucevik the following question: 
  [Begin recording] [Unidentified correspondent] Claims have 
been made to the effect that the bargaining talks on Maras 
[Varosha] will be used on matters related to the economic crisis 
in Turkey. Can you comment on that matter? 
  [Ulucevik] I do not even wish to regard what you have said 
as 
a question. I cannot accept that as a concept. Turkey is well 
aware of its historic responsibilities and obligations toward 
our brethren and kinsmen in Cyprus. That awareness is 
strengthening every day. As I have already said, that cannot be 
accepted as a concept. Nor can any question that is related to 
what you have said be regarded as a proper question. [end 
recording] 

</TEXT>

