<H3> <TI>   U.S. Envoy Lamb Continues Talks on CBM's </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    U.S. Envoy Lamb Continues Talks on CBM's </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Lamb Leaves `Empty-Handed' </H4>

<F P=102> NC1504055194 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 0430 GMT 15 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1504055194 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Robert Lamb, the U.S. State Department's special 
coordinator on the Cyprus issue, left Cyprus empty-handed this 
morning. Lamb had a lengthy meeting with Turkish Cypriot leader 
Rauf Denktas yesterday. 
  In a statement to reporters afterward, Lamb said that 
Denktas 
still has problems with the informal UN document of 21 March. 
Pressured by reporters, the U.S. diplomat said his meetings in 
the occupied area reached no conclusion, adding that he is 
neither a negotiator nor did he bring any new proposals. 

</TEXT>

