<H3> <TI>   Mentese Reports on al-Asad Assurances on PKK </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Mentese Reports on al-Asad Assurances on PKK </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1404164794 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1520 GMT 14 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA1404164794 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ankara, April 14 (A.A.) -- Interior Minister Nahit 
Mentese on Thursday [14 April] said that Syrian President Hafiz 
al-Asad assured him that if necessary PKK [Workers Party of 
Kurdistan] terrorists near the border would be arrested. 
  He was speaking to reporters in the plane on his way back 
from Syria where he met with al-Asad to discuss security issues. 
  Mentese said that he has also asked for the return of the 
chief of the PKK terrorist organization, Abdullah Ocalan. 
  During the three-hour meeting, al-Asad brought up the 
subject 
of water, to which Mentese said that there was no need to worry 
on this issue. 
  He said that he has stressed time and time again that the 
terrorist chief is organizing ethnic groups in Turkey by 
ordering them either from Syria or Lebanon, but al-Asad neither 
confirmed nor rejected this. 
  "At the leaders" level, Turkey has asked for the return of 
the PKK terrorist chief and the members of the terrorist 
organization,' he said. 
  Mentese said Greece is among those backing the PKK and it 
was 
determined that that country is making efforts to hinder Turkish 
tourism and this is an inhuman behavior. 
  "It does not fit friendly or neighborly relations," he 
added. 

</TEXT>

