<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   `At Least' 80 PKK Members Dead in Ongoing Raids </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `At Least' 80 PKK Members Dead in Ongoing Raids </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1404160694 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1545 GMT 14 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA1404160694 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ankara, April 14 (A.A.) -- The Turkish Armed Forces 
struck terrorist bases in northern Iraq's Mezi region and have 
killed at least 80 PKK [Workers Party of Kurdistan] terrorists, 
it was reported on Thursday [14 April]. 
  The Anatolian Agency learned that it was determined that a 
group of 500 to 600 terrorists were preparing to cross the 
border from northern Iraq on April 12. Acting upon this 
information, the Turkish Armed Forces started operations in the 
region with Air Force cover. Chief of Staff Gen. Dogan Gures, 
accompanied by Air Force Commander Gen. Halis Burhan and 
Gendarmerie Force Commander Gen. Aydin Ilter went to Diyarbakir 
earlier in the day. 
  Gures will be briefed on the operations by security forces 
in 
Mezi region as well as in the rural regions of Tendurek, Gabar 
[place-name as received], Diyarbakir and Bingol. 
  Operations are still continuing, officials said. 

</TEXT>

