<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ukrainian Interior Minister Arrives for Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1504071594 Ankara Turkiye Radyolari Network in Turkish 
2000 GMT 14 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1504071594 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara Turkiye Radyolari Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ukrainian Internal Affairs Minister Andriy 
Vasylyshyn, who arrived on an official visit in Ankara today, 
has begun his contacts. He first called on Interior Minister 
Nahit Mentese and conferred with him for some time. Later the 
official talks between the delegations headed by the two 
ministers began. 
  Mentese, in a statement prior to the talks, said that Turkey 
and Ukraine are two friendly, stable, and strong countries in 
the region. He added that a comprehensive and effective 
cooperation between the two countries on international drug 
smuggling, terrorism, and other organized crimes will greatly 
contribute to regional peace. Mentese noted that a crime 
prevention agreement will be signed at the end of the talks. 
  Vasylyshyn said that bilateral cooperation on [words 
indistinct], police training, and scientific research will be 
beneficial for both countries. 

</TEXT>

