<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Demirel Asks Nation To Trust in Secular State </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Demirel Asks Nation To Trust in Secular State </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1404141194 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1200 
GMT 14 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1404141194 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Statement by President Suleyman Demirel, dated 14 April </F>
1994 -- read by announcer over still of Demirel] 
  [Text] Turkey is a constitutional state. The Constitution 
determines the type of state and regime. The state is based on 
rules and institutions. No one has the power to forcibly change 
that. The state has the power and the solutions to protect 
itself, the tranquillity of the people, the democratic regime, 
and the indivisible unity of the country and nation. Everything 
transpires on the basis of the law and of legitimacy. No one 
should even dream of achieving anything by resorting to force or 
by violating the law at the cost of blood and tears. Such 
efforts fall outside the law and legitimacy and are incompatible 
with humanity or a clear conscience. In such cases, the state 
resorts to legitimate measures and solutions to prevent 
violence, brute force, and bloodshed. 
  The state, with all its institutions, is fully aware of its 
duties and ready to carry them out. The people follow 
everything closely. Institutions, establishments, and persons 
who owe their existence to the democratic system should not make 
use of the freedom it gives them to threaten or undermine the 
secular and democratic Turkish Republican State or democracy. 
  I ask my citizens to remain levelheaded in the face of 
irresponsible acts and statements. Everyone must continue to 
trust our state and the secular and democratic Turkish Republic. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-19286 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drweu073_q_94009" </HT>


