<F P=100> INTER-EUROPEAN AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Vranitzky, Mock Ask For EP Support for EU Membership </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Vranitzky, Mock Ask For EP Support for EU Membership </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1404154194 Vienna DER STANDARD in German 14 Apr 94 p 4 </F>
<F P=103> AU1404154194 </F>
<F P=104>  Vienna DER STANDARD </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["norb"-signed report: "Vranitzky and Mock Are Courting </F>
Strasbourg"] 
  [Text] Brussels/Vienna -- Foreign Minister Alois Mock in 
Brussels on Wednesday [13 April] advocated a stronger European 
Parliament [EP]. Austria would actively support this as a 
member of the European Union [EU], Mock said before the group of 
the European People's Party. On the same day, the 800-page text 
of the treaty of accession was delivered to the members of 
parliament. Mock appealed to the deputies: "Vote for Austria 
on 4 May! In this way, you will create the decisive 
prerequisite for us to jointly develop the Europe of tomorrow." 
  Chancellor Franz Vranitzky also wooed the Europeans. In a 
letter, the Social Democratic Party of Austria chairman politely 
asked his party colleagues to advocate sufficient participation 
of the Social Democratic members of the European Parliament in 
the decisive vote. 
  Moreover, Vranitzky asked Vice Chancellor Busek to step in 
for him at the hearing of the four candidate countries before 
the European Parliament in Strasbourg on Tuesday, since he will 
be unable to attend because of his meeting with U.S. President 
Bill Clinton. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

