<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ciller Reports `Fruitful' Meeting With Clinton </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ciller Reports `Fruitful' Meeting With Clinton </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1404184394 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1700 
GMT 14 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1404184394 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Statement to the press by Prime Minister Tansu Ciller </F>
following her meeting with President Bill Clinton at the White 
House -- live] 
  [Text] [Ciller] I reviewed Turkish-U.S. relations with 
President Clinton. We particularly discussed the recent 
incident. I want to take this opportunity to extend my 
condolences to the families of the brave soldiers who lost their 
lives. It is a very regrettable incident. We will study the 
details more closely. Other than that... [pauses] May they 
rest in peace. 
  We discussed other issues as well. We reviewed Turkish-U.S. 
relations. I explained the economic stability program. Mr. 
Clinton clearly said that he will support it. Naturally, we are 
pleased about that. Other than that, we had the opportunity to 
discuss in detail other aspects of Turkey's relations with the 
United States, as well as Bosnia-Herzegovina and Azerbaijan. It 
was a very fruitful meeting. Thank you. 
  [Unidentified reporter] Did you discuss the latest political 
developments in Turkey? 
  [Ciller] Yes, a short assessment of the latest election 
results was made. It was a very fruitful meeting. May it be 
auspicious for our country. 

</TEXT>

