<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   UNHCR Asks Serb Permission To Restart Aid Convoys </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    UNHCR Asks Serb Permission To Restart Aid Convoys </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1504134094 Paris AFP in English 1301 GMT 14 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1504134094 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Geneva, April 15 (AFP) -- The UN High Commissioner 
for Refugees (UNHCR) has asked Bosnian Serb authorities to allow 
aid convoys back on Serb-controlled territory, a UN spokeswoman 
said here Friday [15 April]. 
  Convoys from the Croatian capital Zagreb to Serb-controlled 
Banja Luka in Bosnia-Hercegovina and out of Belgrade in Serbia 
were stopped Monday, as Serb authorities reacted angrily to NATO 
airstrikes Sunday and Monday on Serb positions around the 
besieged Moslem enclave of Gorazde. 
  But UNHCR officials remain in contact with Bosnian Serb 
authorities in Pale, and have asked to restart aid convoys 
through Serb-controlled territory next week, UNHCR spokeswoman 
Sylvana Foa said. 
  Meanwhile, the number of casualities in Gorazde in eastern 
Bosnia since the Serb onslaught began on March 28 rose to 191 
dead and 797 wounded on Thursday, the UN added. 
  The spokeswoman said that according to reports of UNHCR 
staff 
in Gorazde: "People are just incredibly panicked and terrified 
of what is going to happen to them." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

