<F P=104>  Khartoum SUNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Strasbourg 15th April: Speaker of the Transitional 
National Assembly (T.N.A) Mohamed al-Amin Khalifa, who is 
currently leading the Arab Parliamentary Union delegation to the 
European Arab dialogue conference in Strasbourg town, Thursday 
[14th April] met speaker of the European parliamentary assembly. 
  The meetings discussed issues of common concern between the 
Arab world and Europe in addition to reviewing parliamentary 
issues to push forward the parliamentary work and boost 
relations among the countries. 
  The TNA speaker held talks with the sub-committee for 
Middle-East affairs at the European assembly and reviewed [the] 
situation in the Middle East besides Arab-European relations and 
means of future cooperation. 
  It is to be noted that thirteen Arab countries are taking 
part in the conference. 

