<H3> <TI>   Lafontaine Criticizes Government's `Peace Policy' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Lafontaine Criticizes Government's `Peace Policy' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1704151594 Hamburg DPA in German 1135 GMT 17 Apr 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1704151594 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Saarlouis -- Oskar Lafontaine, deputy chairman of 
the Social Democratic Party of Germany [SPD], criticized the 
participation of German soldiers in missions in civil war zones 
as the "wrong peace policy." At a conference of the Saarland 
SPD, Lafontaine stated in Saarlouis today: "Those who want 
peace in Asia and Africa should finally stop exporting weapons 
to these countries." He accused the government of 
schizophrenia, stressing: "First we export our weapons to all 
parts of the world, and then we send our children there as 
soldiers to collect them again." Referring to the civil wars in 
the former Yugoslavia, Somalia, and Rwanda, Lafontaine pointed 
out that it must also be possible to help without soldiers. 

</TEXT>

