<DOCNO> FBIS4-19324 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drweu074__a94012" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-WEU-94-074-A </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  18 April 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Germany </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bonn To Receive 99 Seats in European Parliament </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Bonn To Receive 99 Seats in European Parliament </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1704161694 Hamburg DPA in German 0908 GMT 17 Apr 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1704161694 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bonn -- In the future, Germany will receive 99 
instead of 81 seats in the European Parliament. The planned 
increase in the number of mandates after German unification has 
now been confirmed by the signatures of all 12 member states of 
the European Union, Foreign Minister Klaus Kinkel (Free 
Democratic Party of Germany) announced in Bonn today. The 
increase in the number of seats in the European Parliament, 
which is to be newly elected, will enter into force on 1 May. 

</TEXT>

