evacuate almost 200 Italians from war-torn Rwanda concluded 
Friday [15 April], when 133 Italian troops left the capital 
Kigali and returned to Nairobi, Foreign Ministry sources said. 
  For the past three days the Italians, along with Belgian 
troops, have controlled Kigali airport as part of the operation 
to get European and U.S. nationals out of Rwanda. 

