<H3> <TI>   Cabinet Approves Hebron Observers </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cabinet Approves Hebron Observers </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BR1504093494 Rome ANSAMAIL Database in English 1620 GMT 14 
Apr 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR1504093494 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome ANSAMAIL Database </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Cabinet Approves Italian Presence in </F>
Hebron"] 
  [Text] (ANSA) Rome, 14 April -- A law decree authorising 
the deployment of Italian observers in Hebron in the Israeli 
occupied territories was approved in a cabinet meeting today, 
Education Minister Rosa Russo Jervolino said. 
  The decree states that 35 Italian Armed Forces members and 
technical experts will be sent to Hebron in response to an 
agreement on the issue reached by Israeli and Palestinian 
authorities March 31, on the basis of United Nations Resolution 
904. 
  The scope of the mission, in which Italians will join 60 
Norwegians and 35 Danes, will be "to provide all necessary 
guarantees for the Palestinian people of the occupied 
territories," a cabinet office communique said. 
  The observer mission, dubbed Temporary International 
Presence 
in Hebron (TIPH), will last a minimum three months, and was set 
up after a Jewish settler shot at least 30 Palestinians dead in 
a Hebron mosque February 25. 

</TEXT>

