<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kohl Wants Role as Reliable Partner of Allies </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kohl Wants Role as Reliable Partner of Allies </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1804112294 Cologne Deutschlandfunk Network in German 0900 
GMT 18 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1804112294 </F>
<F P=104>  Cologne Deutschlandfunk Network </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] One day before the hearing of the Federal 
Constitutional Court on armed forces foreign missions, 
Chancellor Kohl has stressed that Germany has to assume 
responsibility at the side of its partners. If peace and 
freedom in the world and Europe are at issue, the FRG must not 
stand aside, Kohl said in Bonn in the morning. 
  During the reception for soldiers who had participated in 
humanitarian and peace missions, the chancellor warned that 
Germany's security and capacity to act in foreign politics are 
based on the allies' confidence. Therefore, the FRG must be a 
reliable partner. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

