<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Urges Responsibility on World Stage </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Urges Responsibility on World Stage </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1804091294 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 0835 GMT 18 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1804091294 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DDP/ADN) -- The day before the Federal 
Constitutional Court hearing on Bundeswehr missions abroad 
begins, Chancellor Helmut Kohl stressed that Germany must take 
responsibility alongside its partners. Germany should not stand 
aside when "peace and freedom in the world and Europe" are at 
stake, Kohl said this morning in Bonn at a reception for 
servicemen who have taken part in humanitarian and peace 
missions. 
  The chancellor recalled that Germany's security and its 
ability to act in foreign policy terms are based on the trust of 
its allies. Therefore, Germany must be "a reliable partner." 
The Bundeswehr's participation in "measures to safeguard world 
peace as part of the international community" is a key issue of 
German foreign and security policy, he said. 

</TEXT>

