<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russian Troops Depart Eberswalde </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russian Troops Depart Eberswalde </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1604124994 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1124 GMT 16 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1604124994 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Eberswalde (DDP/ADN) -- After 49 years on German 
soil, the Russian military officially left the town of 
Eberswalde [near the Polish border] in Barnim district today. 
Apart from a rearguard contingent of just under 200 men, this 
means that between 25,000 and 30,000 Russian military and 
civilian staff from the 20th Guards Unit have now withdrawn. 
The last few are to follow in approximatelty a month. 
  Some 200 local residents turned up at the Russian memorial 
in 
good spring weather to recall those killed during the liberation 
of the town in 1945. Major General Miron Pavlishin spoke at a 
meeting of "good relations" between the military and the local 
people and of a time in Germany that would not be forgotten. He 
expressed hope that friendships would be maintained. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

