<H3> <TI>   Mayor Urges Bosnians To Return, Defend Country </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Mayor Urges Bosnians To Return, Defend Country </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1404182194 Stockholm Radio Sweden in Swedish 1445 GMT 14 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1404182194 </F>
<F P=104>  Stockholm Radio Sweden </F>
<F P=105>  Swedish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] All refugees from Bosnia who are fit to carry arms 
and who are staying in Sweden should travel home and take part 
in the defense of the country, says the Tuzla Mayor Selim 
(?Bezladcic), who is currently visiting Goteborg. According to 
the mayor, within one month the refugees will receive a summons 
to travel home, and that summons will come from the Bosnian 
Government. If they do not heed the call, they may encounter 
problems when they want to return to Bosnia. New passports may 
then be denied them, says the Tuzla mayor, currently visiting 
Goteborg. 

</TEXT>

