<H3> <TI>   Poll: Support for European Union Declines </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Poll: Support for European Union Declines </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1704192394 Helsinki Suomen Yleisradio Network in Finnish 
1800 GMT 17 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1704192394 </F>
<F P=104>  Helsinki Suomen Yleisradio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Finnish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Support for the European Union [EU] is continuing to 
fall in Sweden. According to an opinion poll published in 
GOTEBORGS-POSTEN, supporters of the EU now number 33 percent 
while opponents number 42 percent. The poll also reveals that 
over half of Sweden's Social Democrats are against the EU. This 
is a problem for the party leadership that is in favor of the EU 
and is seeking to gain governmental powers in the Swedish 
elections in September. 

</TEXT>

