<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Provocation' in Buffer Zone Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Provocation' in Buffer Zone Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1604190794 Nicosia CyBC Television Network in Greek 1818 
GMT 16 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1604190794 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia CyBC Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ladies and Gentlemen, we now broadcast an emergency 
report that we have just received. A new Turkish provocation 
took place in Nicosia today at 1430 GMT this afternoon. 
According to information obtained by CyBC [Cyprus Broadcasting 
Corporation], near Famagusta Gate a Turkish soldier left his 
guardpost, entered a prohibited area of the buffer zone, and 
headed toward a National Guard guardpost. A national guardsman 
called on the Turkish soldier to leave the area immediately. 
The Turkish soldier did not obey and the national guardsman was 
forced to fire warning shots into the air. The Turkish soldier 
then withdrew. 
  Defense Minister Konstandinos Iliadhis told CyBC just a 
short 
while ago that the republic's authorities strongly protested to 
UNFICYP [UN Force in Cyprus] on the new Turkish provocation. An 
UNFICYP spokesman told CyBC that the incident is under 
investigation. It is not serious, he said. 
  The illegal Turkish Cypriot radio station [Bayrak] concealed 
the Turkish side's attempt to cause tension and reported that a 
Greek Cypriot national guardsman provoked a Turkish soldier by 
firing shots against his guardpost. 
  It is now calm in the area but the National Guard is 
following the situation closely. 

</TEXT>

