<H3> <TI>   Mentese Warns Against Illegal Demonstrations </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Mentese Warns Against Illegal Demonstrations </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1704140194 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1000 
GMT 17 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1704140194 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over still of Mentese] </F>
  [Text] Interior Minister Nahit Mentese has said that 
everyone has the right to organize meetings and demonstrations 
in line with the freedom of expression and of thought, adding 
that, however, this should be done within the framework of the 
law. 
  Mentese issued a statement in connection with demonstrations 
held in certain cities in recent days disrupting public order. 
He said that marches and rallies might be curbed with the aim 
of securing public order and preventing the disruption of city 
security. Pointing out that the way in which rallies and 
demonstration can be held are stipulated by the Constitution and 
the law, Mentese said: Everyone should be aware that the rights 
and freedoms granted to individuals and democratic organizations 
through the law, can be curtailed or banned -- without damaging 
the essence of the fundamental rights and freedoms -- in the 
event laws are trespassed or crimes committed while these rights 
and freedoms are being exercised. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

