<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry on Greek-Albanian Incident </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Ministry on Greek-Albanian Incident </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1504195594 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1700 
GMT 15 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1504195594 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report] </F>
  [Text] Turkey has announced that in the existing sensitive 
atmosphere in the region, it is important that all Balkan 
countries refrain from actions that will further strain existing 
tensions. 
  In reply to a question, Foreign Ministry spokesman Ferhat 
Ataman said that reports on a raid organized on 10 April against 
a military training camp on Albanian territory near the Greek 
border cause regret and concern for the future of the region. 
Expressing understanding for the concern felt by Albania in the 
face of provocations and threats, Ataman remarked that countries 
that plan to pressure their neighbors through the actions of 
terrorist groups should realize that they cannot be left out of 
the negative developments that stem from such provocations. 

</TEXT>

