<H3> <TI>   Death Toll Reaches 57 in Hakkari Operations </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Death Toll Reaches 57 in Hakkari Operations </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1704153994 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1500 
GMT 17 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1704153994 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over still of regional map] </F>
  [Text] The operations launched by the security forces 
south of Hakkari's Cukurca District on 12 April against 
terrorists trying to infiltrate into Turkey are continuing. So 
far 57 terrorists have been killed in these operations. The 
operations being conducted by the Hakkari mountain commando 
units are, at times, being supported by aircraft. 
  According to information obtained from Turkish Radio and 
Television correspondent Bahadir Serif Onari, nine mortars, 
three machine guns, 16 Kalashnikovs, 152,000 rounds of 
ammunition, mortar shells, rockets, 98 hand grenades, 48 mines, 
radios and electronic equipment have been seized. Eight tonnes 
of foodstuff found in the caves belonging to the terrorists have 
been destroyed. 

</TEXT>

