<F P=100> FRANCE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Leotard Comments on Gorazde Situation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Leotard Comments on Gorazde Situation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1504224894 Paris France-Inter Radio Network in French 2200 
GMT 15 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1504224894 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris France-Inter Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Serb forces have taken control of most strategic 
points surrounding Gorazde. This has resulted in a mass exodus 
of civilians toward the city center, to where the small UN 
contingent has also withdrawn. One of the British soldiers 
seriously wounded this evening has died of his injuries. In 
Washington, President Clinton said tonight that one should be 
firm with the Serbs but avoid provocation. This evening the 
defense minister, Francois Leotard, reacted too: 
  [Begin Leotard recording] The behavior of the Serb side is 
extremely worrying. It is the continuation of ethnic cleansing 
in Gorazde, as in Sarajevo, as elsewhere. This is unacceptable 
for the international community and for France. Our soldiers 
are there to end the acts of violence and hatred which run 
against the grain of European culture. We fervently wish that, 
through the talks currently underway, the Serb side will 
understand that it cannot win through force, and in the face of 
the international community territorial and other gains rejected 
by the other parties. France will continue to try, with special 
care, through its presence on the ground, through its diplomats 
and the action of its foreign minister, Alain Juppe, to obtain a 
peace settlement, which represents the only solution to this 
conflict. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

