<F P=101> Finland </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government To Send UN Observers to South Africa </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government To Send UN Observers to South Africa </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1504151994 Helsinki Suomen Yleisradio Network in Finnish 
1000 GMT 15 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1504151994 </F>
<F P=104>  Helsinki Suomen Yleisradio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Finnish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Finland will send 45 UN observers to South Africa's 
first democratic elections. Representatives of all races in 
South Africa are allowed to vote in these elections during the 
last week of this month. Finland will send 15 observers to 
South Africa, and they will be placed under the United Nations. 
In addition, the Foreign Ministry has hired 30 observers 
directly for the UN. The first Finnish group of observers will 
leave for South Africa on 17 April. 

</TEXT>

