<H3> <TI>   Kozyrev Welcomes Paris Initiative for Bosnia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kozyrev Welcomes Paris Initiative for Bosnia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1404154494 Paris AFP in English 1509 GMT 14 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1404154494 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Paris, April 14 (AFP) -- Russian Foreign Minister 
Andrey Kozyrev on Thursday [14 April] welcomed a French proposal 
for relaunching peace negotiations on former Yugoslavia, the 
French Foreign Ministry said. 
  Spokesman Richard Duque said French Foreign Minister Alain 
Juppe spoke by telephone with Kozyrev on Thursday to discuss the 
situation in the besieged Moslem enclave of Gorazde in Bosnia. 
  Kozyrev was "very positive" on a French proposal for a 
"partnership" of the European Union, Russia and the United 
States to restart the Bosnia peace conference, currently chaired 
by the EU [European Union] and the United Nations, Duque said. 
  Juppe also discussed a French draft resolution at the UN 
Security Council on Gorazde, demanding a ceasefire and 
deployment of UN peacekeepers in the enclave, the spokesman said. 

</TEXT>

