<F P=100> FRANCE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Mitterrand, Latvia's Ulmanis Hold Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Mitterrand, Latvia's Ulmanis Hold Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1304190994 Riga Radio Riga Network in Latvian 1700 GMT 13 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1304190994 </F>
<F P=104>  Riga Radio Riga Network </F>
<F P=105>  Latvian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] During a meeting with French President Francois 
Mitterrand in Paris on Tuesday [12 April] evening, Latvian 
President Guntis Ulmanis expressed readiness for integration 
into the European Union [EU] and a willingness to implement EU 
requirements. However, Ulmanis stressed, Europe will have to 
rely more on Latvia in the integration process. 
  It is important that both Denmark and France are ready to 
discuss the issue of setting up a fund to support the closure of 
the Skrunda radar base and for the repatriation of Russian 
military pensioners to Russia, according to Martins Virsis, 
parliamentary secretary of the Latvian Ministry of Foreign 
Affairs. 
  Francois Mitterrand admitted during the talks that Latvias 
is 
a small nation but has a unique European culture. Europe is 
interested in preserving countries like that, Mitterrand said. 

</TEXT>

