<F P=100> FRANCE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Air France Loss of 8-9 Billion Francs Predicted </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Air France Loss of 8-9 Billion Francs Predicted </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1404152694 Paris AFP in English 1425 GMT 14 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1404152694 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Paris, April 14 (AFP) -- Air France will probably 
report a loss of eight billion to nine billion francs ($1.37 to 
1.54 billion) for 1993, French transport minister Bernard Bosson 
told the Senate on Thursday [14 April]. 
  He said the troubled airline would announce the figure 
"within a few days," adding that airline "officials informed the 
government after a substantial delay." 
  The most recent official forecast was for a loss of 7.5 
billion francs last year. 
  Bosson added that the government would grant 20 billion 
francs' worth of aid to the company in three installments over 
three years, "depending on concrete results" of the airline's 
recovery efforts. The first half (10 billion francs) will be 
paid after the European Commission in Brussels approves the 
company's restructuring plans, he said. 

</TEXT>

