<F P=102>   LD1504192494 Hilversum Radio Netherlands in English 1739 GMT 
15 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1504192494 </F>
<F P=104>  Hilversum Radio Netherlands </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Dutch Foreign Minister Peter Kooijmans has expressed 
concern at the capture in Bosnia of around 200 UN personnel. 
Among them are three Dutch nationals. They have been taken 
hostage by Serbs in actions following NATO air strikes against 
Serb positions near Gorazde. Mr. Kooijmans emphasized that the 
air strikes were in accordance with a UN resolution, and he 
called the Serb reaction completely unjustified. 

</TEXT>

