<H3> <TI>   Butrus-Ghali Warns of Possible Further NATO Strikes </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Butrus-Ghali Warns of Possible Further NATO Strikes </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1404140294 Paris AFP in English 1343 GMT 14 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1404140294 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Madrid, April 14 (AFP) -- UN Secretary General 
Butrus Butrus-Ghali said Thursday [14 April] he would "not 
hesitate" to ask NATO forces to carry out new air strikes if UN 
peacekeepers were endangered in ex-Yugoslavia. 
  The UN chief told a news conference: "We have the 
responsibility to protect the security of our United Nations 
troops in former Yugoslavia, and we will not hesitate to ask for 
an air support in case that the security of the United Nations 
forces, among which (are) Spanish troops, is in danger." 
  He spoke alongside Spanish Foreign Minister Javier Solana 
after arriving here late Wednesday from Germany for a three-day 
official visit. 
  Butrus-Ghali recalled that the UN Security Council had 
unanimously approved Resolution 836, which constitutes the legal 
basis for North Atlantic Treaty Organization air strikes. 
[passage omitted] 

