<H3> <TI>   Government To Withdraw Blue Helmets From Rwanda </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government To Withdraw Blue Helmets From Rwanda </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1504132294 Brussels Radio 1 Network in Dutch 1300 GMT 15 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1504132294 </F>
<F P=104>  Brussels Radio 1 Network </F>
<F P=105>  Dutch </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Belgium is withdrawing its blue helmets from Rwanda. 
This has just been decided by the Council of Ministers. The 
government will however consult with the United Nations about 
the practical implementation of that decision. 
  The Council of Ministers judges that the UN mission in 
Rwanda 
has become pointless. Because of the recent dramatic events, 
the peace and democatization process in Rwanda has come to an 
end. That is why the government urges the suspension of the UN 
mandate. Moreover, the anti-Belgian witch-hunt makes the work of 
the blue helmets impossible, the Council of Ministers argues. 

</TEXT>

