<F P=100> ITALY &amp; VATICAN CITY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Prime Minister Ciampi Submits Resignation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Prime Minister Ciampi Submits Resignation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1604180594 Paris AFP in English 1749 GMT 16 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1604180594 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Rome, April 16 (AFP) -- Prime Minister Carlo Azeglio 
Ciampi handed in his resignation to President Oscar Luigi 
Scalfaro on Saturday [16 April], the premier's office announced. 
  Ciampi, 73, said last week he was ready to resign after the 
March 27-28 general election but would do so only after the 
election of the speakers of the upper and lower houses of 
parliament. Politicians from the right-wing Freedom Alliance 
[Carlo Scognamiglio and Irene Pivetti respectively] were voted 
into the posts earlier Saturday. 

</TEXT>

