<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Scognamiglio Elected Senate Speaker in Fourth Ballot </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1604155894 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 1538 GMT 
16 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1604155894 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Televideo Teletext </F>
<F P=105>  Italian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Carlo Scognamiglio is the new speaker of the Senate. 
The candidate of the majority parties (Freedom Alliance) was 
elected in the fourth ballot with 162 votes. Spadolini won 161 
votes. 
  [Rome TV Teletext in Italian at 0919 GMT on 16 Apr 94 
reported that at the third ballot, Carlo Scognamiglio and 
Giovanni Spadolini polled 159 votes each. As provided in the 
rules for the election of the Senate speaker, there will 
therefore be a further vote between the two, which is scheduled 
for this afternoon. The details of the third ballot are as 
follows: 
Scognamiglio, 159 votes; Spadolini, 159 votes; Cossiga, 2 votes. 
  [There were four blank papers. The attendance and the voters 
numbered 324. The required number of votes for election is 
163.] 

</TEXT>

