  [Text] Silvio Berlusconi has once again invited the PPI 
[Italian People's Party] to talks. Berlusconi said: I would be 
happy if a political force we have always looked to, and with a 
program very close to our own, accepted to sit down at a table 
with us to find out what we could do together in parliament. 
Berlusconi added: I do not even rule out a possible government 
pact. 
  Rocco Buttiglione lost no time in replying. He said that he 
appreciated Berlusconi's opening out toward them, but added: I 
cannot understand why the invitation to talks should concern 
only the matter of the Senate speaker and not the speaker of the 
Chamber of Deputies as well. 
  [National Alliance leader] Gianfranco Fini has said no to 
any 
talks. The National Alliance leader commented: I cannot 
imagine a government involving the PPI and Forza Italia. 

