<F P=100> ITALY &amp; VATICAN CITY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Berlusconi: Government Must Have Majority To Govern </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Berlusconi: Government Must Have Majority To Govern </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1504141094 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 1200 GMT 
15 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1504141094 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Televideo Teletext </F>
<F P=105>  Italian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] "A government cannot govern if its policies are not 
accepted in both chambers of parliament. Were that to happen, 
there would be no other solution than to go back to the 
electorate with a majority that would be confirmed and 
strengthened by the experience. I hope this does not prove 
necessary." Silvio Berlusconi has thus added his voice to those 
who think there might be a new general election if Giovanni 
Spadolini were to win. 
  Earlier the Northern League's Roberto Maroni had warned: We 
will have another general election and "we will say that the PDS 
[Democratic Party of the Left] and the PPI [Italian Popular 
Party] were in cahoots to bring the institutions to a standstill 
and we will ask the nation for greater power." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

