<F P=100> ITALY &amp; VATICAN CITY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Scalfaro Responds, Berlusconi Clarifies </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Scalfaro Responds, Berlusconi Clarifies </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1604132194 Rome RAI Due Television Network in Italian 1100 
GMT 16 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1604132194 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Due Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Italian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] [Passage omitted] A general election has been 
threatened in the event of the government majority not 
controlling both the Senate and the Chamber of Deputies. This 
morning, President Oscar Luigi Scalfaro commented on this. 
  [Unidentified correspondent] To threaten to partially or 
completely dissolve parliament would be a serious error because 
it would impinge on the head of state's legal competence. This 
is how the president's office has replied to members of the 
majority parties who stressed the problems the new government 
would have if there were two different majorities in the two 
chambers of parliament. In the face of this criticism, Forza 
Italia leader Silvio Berlusconi has sought to clarify his 
position: 
  [Begin Berlusconi recording] I said that it was clear that 
in 
order for a government to govern it must have the two chambers 
of parliament on its side. If the situation were to arise in 
one of the two chambers where a majority close to the government 
could not be found, it would be impossible to govern. [end 
recording] 
  According to the Northern League's Roberto Maroni, who has 
made the same points as Berlusconi, the presidency has not 
understood the gist of his argument. He has denied threatening 
to dissolve parliament. 
  Christian Democratic Center party leader Pierferdinando 
Casinis said his were only political observations. 
  For the Progressive Alliance, Achille Occhetto [Democratic 
Party of the Left leader] commented: 
  [Begin Occhetto recording] I think it was his duty. The head 
of state has simply said that only he and no one else can 
dissolve parliament. [end recording] [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

