<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   EU Calls For International Aid For Rwanda </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    EU Calls For International Aid For Rwanda </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1804190894 Paris AFP in English 1857 GMT 18 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1804190894 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Luxembourg, April 18 (AFP) -- The European Union 
called here Monday [18 April] for an international programme of 
humanitarian aid in response to the "human tragedy" in Rwanda, 
and said it was ready to take part. 
  A statement issued during a meeting of EU foreign ministers 
also appealed to the warring Hutu and Tutsi tribes in Rwanda to 
stop fighting and resume negotiations under the Arusha accord 
signed in August last year. 
  The accord provides a framework for a negotiated settlement 
leading to democratic elections that would bring the minority 
Tutsis into government. 
  Tens of thousands of people have been killed and wounded in 
Rwanda since inter-tribal bloodshed resumed on April 6. 

</TEXT>

